1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,625
<i>He seemed clumsy and careless,</i>

2
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:16,166
<i>but he was actually very observant.</i>

3
00:00:16,708 --> 00:00:17,958
IN MEMORY OF MR. CHENG KUANG-CHI

4
00:00:18,041 --> 00:00:22,000
Kuang-chi might have seemed
to be bold and fearless,

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:27,208
but I know his biggest fear
was his daughter being unhappy.

6
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:29,708
Here's the thing about him.

7
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:34,291
He kept asking me to teach him
how to make tomato omelet rice.

8
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:35,958
I'd have taught him,

9
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:38,708
but you know how he was.

10
00:00:38,791 --> 00:00:41,041
He was only good
at making instant noodles.

11
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:44,541
Kuang-Chi

12
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:48,416
was the best and most loyal friend

13
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,166
I've ever had in my life.

14
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:55,583
Last time, at Tang's funeral,

15
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:58,416
I think I also said this about Tang.

16
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:02,916
I said,

17
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:05,666
"People our age

18
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:07,541
seem to be attending

19
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:11,208
more funerals than birthday parties."

20
00:01:11,708 --> 00:01:12,875
But Kuang-chi said,

21
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:19,708
"Now there are fewer of us
attending these events."

22
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,791
Safe journey.

23
00:01:29,916 --> 00:01:33,000
<i>Kuang-chi was</i>
<i>a humorous and easygoing person.</i>

24
00:01:33,083 --> 00:01:35,916
He just went ahead
to scout the way for us.

25
00:01:36,541 --> 00:01:38,000
Next, let's invite

26
00:01:38,083 --> 00:01:40,708
his long-time close friend,

27
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:45,666
Ms. Hsiu-lien, to come up
and share her moments with Kuang-chi.

28
00:01:47,416 --> 00:01:49,833
Hello, I'm Liu Hsiu-lien.

29
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:53,666
I'm not dressed like this
because I'm rude.

30
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:57,916
It's because
this dress was Kuang-chi's favorite.

31
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,333
Whenever I had it on,

32
00:01:59,416 --> 00:02:00,875
he'd compliment me.

33
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:03,708
So for his funeral,

34
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:05,625
I wanted to put it on

35
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,541
so he could enjoy it

36
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:11,708
and praise me again.

37
00:02:14,416 --> 00:02:16,666
Not a lot of you know this,

38
00:02:18,875 --> 00:02:22,666
but I almost married Kuang-chi.

39
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:26,166
When we were out on a date,

40
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:28,541
Kuang-chi ruined the moment by saying,

41
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:31,250
"I want to get married
so that when I'm old,

42
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:34,041
someone can care for me. That's all."

43
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:35,875
He also said

44
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:39,375
that he didn't want
his daughter to worry about him.

45
00:02:41,708 --> 00:02:43,041
But then I thought,

46
00:02:44,083 --> 00:02:46,583
"For when you're old? Aren't you old now?"

47
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:51,500
But if you came out of your coffin now

48
00:02:52,875 --> 00:02:54,541
and asked me to marry you,

49
00:02:55,916 --> 00:02:58,500
I'd still say no.

50
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:02,333
Ms. Hsiu-lien,
thank you for the heartfelt speech.

51
00:03:02,416 --> 00:03:05,375
Now let's invite
another close friend of Kuang-chi,

52
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:08,416
Ms. Wang Mei-huei, to speak to us.

53
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,916
Are you sure?

54
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:17,000
All right. Next, let's invite
Mr. Chang Kai.

55
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:25,333
Hello, I'm Chang Kai.

56
00:03:26,458 --> 00:03:28,208
I was Mr. Cheng Kuang-chi's…

57
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:31,250
close friend, I think.

58
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:33,416
Just joking.

59
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:35,125
But I actually am.

60
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:36,541
It's unfortunate.

61
00:03:36,625 --> 00:03:40,250
I never imagine I'd see Le-le's dad
for the last time like this.

62
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:43,125
He was not only my in-law

63
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,583
but also my friend, despite the age gap.

64
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:48,250
He was optimistic by nature.

65
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:53,166
I think his liveliness and high spirits
surpassed that of many young people.

66
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:57,083
I'd like to share a short story.

67
00:03:58,583 --> 00:04:00,833
Le-le's dad used to tell me in private

68
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:05,208
he was grateful
I took Le-le off his hands.

69
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,875
But I'd like to use this opportunity

70
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,375
to tell him

71
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:13,625
that I was the grateful one.

72
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,583
I'd like to thank him
for entrusting Le-Le to me.

73
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,666
But I didn't know any better

74
00:04:20,416 --> 00:04:21,500
and gave Le-le back.

75
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,375
Despite all that,

76
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:29,333
the connection between him and me
will never disappear.

77
00:04:29,916 --> 00:04:31,708
We are the two people in the world…

78
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,833
who love Le-le the most.

79
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:38,583
Thank you.

80
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:47,541
Friends and family of Mr. Cheng,
thank you all

81
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:51,750
for sharing and looking back
on various aspects of Kuang-chi's life.

82
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,083
So, to close the funeral today,

83
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:58,125
we'd like Mr. Cheng's
most beloved daughter, Cheng Le-le,

84
00:04:58,208 --> 00:05:01,083
to share her thoughts on her father.

85
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:23,375
RAIN THAT WON'T STOP ANYTIME SOON

86
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:28,083
EMERGENCY DEPARTMENT INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

87
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:41,041
Buddha, Guanyin,
Jesus Christ, Virgin Mary,

88
00:05:42,416 --> 00:05:44,291
watch over him…

89
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:54,833
Dad.

90
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:59,333
If you're in pain and want to go,

91
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:03,208
just go ahead. Don't worry about me.

92
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,833
Mr. Cheng, you're awake?

93
00:06:25,416 --> 00:06:26,333
Dad.

94
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:32,833
Just…

95
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,375
Just now,

96
00:06:35,083 --> 00:06:37,750
I was already at death's door.

97
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,750
Then I saw you there,

98
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,166
scolding me.

99
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,375
I was so scared

100
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,083
that I came back.

101
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:53,958
Your dad's adorable.

102
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:56,958
There's always a catch
with every adorable person.

103
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:06,041
We'd like Mr. Cheng's
most beloved daughter, Cheng Le-le,

104
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:09,125
to share her thoughts on her father.

105
00:07:27,958 --> 00:07:29,375
Are you kidding me?

106
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:30,541
- Hey…
- Kuang-chi.

107
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:32,375
So you knew?

108
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:34,000
Why the tears?

109
00:07:34,875 --> 00:07:35,875
Kuang-chi.

110
00:07:35,958 --> 00:07:38,166
- You freaked me out.
- That was freaky.

111
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,041
I was freaked out.

112
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:41,250
What an old rascal.

113
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,250
- Oh boy.
- What the hell was that?

114
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:51,875
Thank you for coming today.

115
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:55,458
I've missed you all so much.

116
00:07:57,250 --> 00:08:00,416
When I heard what everyone just said,

117
00:08:00,916 --> 00:08:02,791
I really thought this…

118
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:15,291
Well,

119
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:17,500
I've never died before

120
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:19,958
so I don't know

121
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:23,500
what it's like to be

122
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,041
in a coffin,

123
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:28,125
or if I can hear people talking.

124
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:31,375
So my daughter and I

125
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:33,625
came up with this little plot.

126
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:34,708
Sorry about that.

127
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:37,458
You're such a prankster.

128
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,625
I'm glad you're okay.

129
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,583
I've been willful all my life.

130
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:50,458
I'm not a great dad,

131
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:53,583
or a good husband.

132
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,416
As a friend,

133
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,416
I'm not really reliable.

134
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:01,458
As for my jobs,

135
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,625
I was a jack of all trades,
master of none.

136
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,500
I wanted to do everything.

137
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:08,875
Enough of that.

138
00:09:11,291 --> 00:09:14,000
I didn't get to be a good son either.

139
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:18,333
Of course, I wasn't a good lover.

140
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,250
But I suppose

141
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:27,083
I'm a good person.

142
00:09:32,166 --> 00:09:33,625
All my life,

143
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:36,125
I feared having regrets.

144
00:09:36,958 --> 00:09:39,208
But because of that,

145
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:42,916
I ended up letting lots of people down.

146
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:48,333
When I heard what you guys just said,

147
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:51,125
I realized

148
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,500
that kicking the bucket

149
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,750
has a big perk.

150
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:04,416
Everyone says nice things about you
and all memories became wonderful.

151
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:12,000
Le-le,

152
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,541
I've always said,

153
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:18,083
if the sky falls,
tall people will hold it up.

154
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,416
You've always said,

155
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,958
"What if the tall people just duck?"

156
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:28,333
What will you do then?

157
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:31,375
Listen,

158
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:34,458
I'll be watching over you

159
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:36,208
from up in the sky.

160
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:45,750
So don't be afraid.

161
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,291
I'll be watching over you.

162
00:10:57,291 --> 00:11:01,125
IN LOVING MEMORY OF MR. CHENG KUANG-CHI

163
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:19,708
I wanted to give you a heads-up.

164
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,458
Even if I knew,

165
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:27,791
I'd still show up.

166
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:35,916
Do you think we should hurry up

167
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,291
and get our divorce finalized?

168
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,708
I can ask to be relocated back.

169
00:11:59,583 --> 00:12:00,625
Why would you?

170
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:02,375
Get out of here.

171
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:05,083
I can't even handle my dad.

172
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:09,000
I'm really glad we didn't have kids.

173
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:11,000
If we did, things would've been

174
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:12,791
too much to handle.

175
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,250
If anything really happened to my dad,

176
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:19,833
all that miscellaneous stuff…

177
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,583
I'll do whatever you want.

178
00:12:29,541 --> 00:12:31,416
If you need help financially--

179
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,125
It's all good.

180
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:37,458
But thank you.

181
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:45,708
Le-le.

182
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:49,791
Can you not always act so tough?

183
00:12:54,791 --> 00:12:56,041
Cheng Kuang-chi is

184
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,041
really crazy, right?

185
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,916
Like father, like daughter.

186
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,541
Hey, what do you mean?

187
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:08,916
Aren't you just as crazy
to have arranged this funeral for him?

188
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:13,041
Do you think I can stop him
from doing anything he wants?

189
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,833
IN LOVING MEMORY OF MR. CHENG KUANG-CHI

190
00:13:24,708 --> 00:13:26,250
All right, that's enough.

191
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:28,125
You barely took five steps.

192
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,416
I'm tired. I want to sit down.

193
00:13:31,291 --> 00:13:32,208
Ten more steps.

194
00:13:32,291 --> 00:13:34,125
Mr. Cheng, time for your pills.

195
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:35,625
Here.

196
00:13:36,458 --> 00:13:38,458
- Five steps.
- Are you haggling now?

197
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:39,458
Seven steps.

198
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:42,708
You can have ice cream later.

199
00:13:42,791 --> 00:13:44,750
Okay. Fine, I'll take them.

200
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,458
You can do it. You're doing well today.

201
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,250
Yes, good boy!

202
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:51,375
One more step.

203
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:55,166
Nice. Good boy, Cheng Kuang-chi.

204
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,791
Why do you sound like
you're talking to a dog?

205
00:13:57,875 --> 00:13:59,541
Come on, even a dog walks faster.

206
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:01,416
That might be an insult to dogs.

207
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,208
Come on, faster.

208
00:14:07,375 --> 00:14:09,625
Don't just pick the big ones.

209
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:15,041
You only pick the big ones.

210
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:40,250
Dad, you… Hey!

211
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:41,833
Hey, wait.

212
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,583
I'm exhausted.

213
00:14:43,666 --> 00:14:46,083
You're just messing around, aren't you?

214
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:48,208
- One last step?
- The last step.

215
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,833
- Okay.
- The last step. Come.

216
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:53,083
Good job!

217
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:55,958
- Mr. Cheng Kuang-chi is awesome.
- Gosh.

218
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:57,291
Ice cream.

219
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:58,916
- You're the best.
- Really?

220
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,375
And at this place,

221
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:03,583
you don't have to pay
at the grocery stores

222
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:07,333
because all the cashiers are caregivers.

223
00:15:07,416 --> 00:15:09,041
They will say,

224
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:12,208
"You don't have to pay
because someone has paid."

225
00:15:12,291 --> 00:15:13,666
Those seniors will say,

226
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,458
"That's nice."

227
00:15:18,416 --> 00:15:19,291
It wasn't funny?

228
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:23,875
I have to stay focused
to walk a straight line.

229
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:28,166
This is so good.

230
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,125
Yeah.

231
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:32,458
Well, can you always get me ice cream

232
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:34,875
after my rehab exercise?

233
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:37,041
You wish.

234
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:38,708
Here, I'll take a photo of you.

235
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:43,625
Let me post a story.

236
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:50,000
Gosh… Again?

237
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:52,750
Come on.

238
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:56,875
Good boy.

239
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,875
I'm all better. Why take so many pills?

240
00:17:07,583 --> 00:17:08,541
I'm home.

241
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:15,458
Dad, what are you doing?

242
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,333
Dad.

243
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,666
Do you need help?

244
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:25,833
Dad.

245
00:17:26,958 --> 00:17:28,541
Can I come in?

246
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,375
Let me know if you need any help.

247
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:11,625
Dad.

248
00:18:11,708 --> 00:18:14,583
Listen, I have to head out.

249
00:18:14,666 --> 00:18:17,416
And I'll be back in just three hours.

250
00:18:17,916 --> 00:18:20,333
I really need to go out and work.

251
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:21,583
Yeah?

252
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:22,500
Okay.

253
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:25,750
Here, just listen to music and watch TV.

254
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:29,333
I'll be back in just three hours.

255
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:34,041
Be right back.

256
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:01,708
<i>Thank you for the second chance.</i>

257
00:19:01,791 --> 00:19:03,875
Oh well, someone got Covid again.

258
00:19:04,791 --> 00:19:05,708
Got your script?

259
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:08,625
I forgot to print it out,
but I've saved it on my phone.

260
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:10,041
- Take a look.
- It's fine.

261
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:12,583
- Just go ahead. What's the topic?
- Nursing home.

262
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:14,125
- That's boring.
- It's not.

263
00:19:14,208 --> 00:19:16,541
It's fascinating.
It's a place in the Netherlands.

264
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:19,708
They built a retirement village
for dementia patients.

265
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:22,208
Those patients
don't know they have dementia.

266
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:24,125
And they're monitored 24/7.

267
00:19:24,208 --> 00:19:25,875
Seriously, it's fascinating.

268
00:19:25,958 --> 00:19:26,875
Keep going.

269
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,500
I'll bring up my dad
to introduce the topic.

270
