How do you make it here without me?

526
00:36:53,958 --> 00:36:56,958
We don't get any sun when you're not here.

527
00:36:57,041 --> 00:36:58,416
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

528
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:00,791
- Here, I'll do it.
- Okay.

529
00:37:04,500 --> 00:37:06,791
Dad, are you hungry?

530
00:37:07,458 --> 00:37:08,875
Do you want some food?

531
00:37:09,375 --> 00:37:10,916
Or do you want water?

532
00:37:11,625 --> 00:37:12,791
No?

533
00:37:14,083 --> 00:37:15,041
Here.

534
00:37:15,125 --> 00:37:17,583
I got you some information
on nursing homes.

535
00:37:17,666 --> 00:37:18,500
Okay.

536
00:37:18,583 --> 00:37:19,541
This is for you.

537
00:37:20,750 --> 00:37:23,333
I've highlighted
the ones that are affordable.

538
00:37:23,833 --> 00:37:26,083
I regretted it
after talking to you that day.

539
00:37:26,166 --> 00:37:28,125
You don't need to decide now.

540
00:37:28,208 --> 00:37:31,833
If possible,
check out the homes with your dad.

541
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:33,875
He should have a say in this too.

542
00:37:34,583 --> 00:37:37,083
Despite it all,
I still find this so cruel.

543
00:37:37,916 --> 00:37:39,166
Cruel?

544
00:37:39,833 --> 00:37:41,208
How is it cruel?

545
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,458
At least these nursing homes
have professional caregivers.

546
00:37:45,541 --> 00:37:47,791
You got hurt taking care of him.

547
00:37:49,666 --> 00:37:51,000
You've done your best.

548
00:37:52,125 --> 00:37:53,666
I haven't.

549
00:37:55,750 --> 00:37:57,500
I know I haven't.

550
00:38:00,291 --> 00:38:02,500
Think about it. When my mom abandoned us,

551
00:38:02,583 --> 00:38:04,458
my dad, this big man, he…

552
00:38:05,583 --> 00:38:09,250
Now I have a little setback,
and I want to send him to a nursing home.

553
00:38:09,750 --> 00:38:12,416
You know,
I shouldn't even have such thoughts.

554
00:38:20,250 --> 00:38:22,166
Ma'am, would you like some milk?

555
00:38:23,291 --> 00:38:24,458
Wait a second.

556
00:38:26,250 --> 00:38:28,375
Why does it seem so easy for others?

557
00:38:28,458 --> 00:38:30,083
Just like I said.

558
00:38:30,666 --> 00:38:31,875
They are professionals.

559
00:38:32,958 --> 00:38:36,208
You should really find a higher-paying job

560
00:38:36,291 --> 00:38:38,750
and send your dad to a nursing home.

561
00:38:38,833 --> 00:38:40,333
These facilities are good.

562
00:38:44,916 --> 00:38:46,125
It's so sunny today.

563
00:38:48,625 --> 00:38:51,291
Dad, why don't we go home now?

564
00:38:52,458 --> 00:38:53,625
Let's go.

565
00:38:54,291 --> 00:38:56,583
Can you please not send me away?

566
00:39:03,666 --> 00:39:05,750
Please don't send me away.

567
00:39:21,625 --> 00:39:24,250
Can you please not send me away?

568
00:39:24,333 --> 00:39:26,041
I can really look after myself.

569
00:39:26,125 --> 00:39:29,083
But please don't send me
to the neighbor's again. Is that okay?

570
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:37,666
<i>Okay.</i>

571
00:39:42,625 --> 00:39:43,500
Pinky swear.

572
00:39:58,375 --> 00:39:59,375
Get a bit closer.

573
00:40:05,750 --> 00:40:10,291
<i>Number 55,</i>
<i>please come to counter 16. Thank you.</i>

574
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,208
<i>How may I help you?</i>

575
00:40:12,791 --> 00:40:13,666
Divorce.

576
00:40:14,458 --> 00:40:18,000
I'll need your household registry,
ID cards, and name chops.

577
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
CHANG KAI

578
00:40:21,083 --> 00:40:24,166
CHENG LE-LE

579
00:40:28,291 --> 00:40:29,458
Just a moment.

580
00:40:56,125 --> 00:40:57,625
What time is your flight?

581
00:40:59,458 --> 00:41:00,458
7:50 p.m.

582
00:41:03,916 --> 00:41:05,791
Congratulations, you're single.

583
00:41:07,500 --> 00:41:08,416
Yeah.

584
00:41:09,333 --> 00:41:10,416
A dream life.

585
00:41:20,375 --> 00:41:21,833
All right, well…

586
00:41:22,458 --> 00:41:23,708
Safe flight tonight.

587
00:41:24,875 --> 00:41:25,791
Take care.

588
00:41:29,458 --> 00:41:31,041
Bye, eligible bachelor.

589
00:42:07,083 --> 00:42:10,041
Dad, we're now going to get into bed.

590
00:42:10,125 --> 00:42:11,041
Hold on to me.

591
00:42:12,041 --> 00:42:12,958
Hold on tight.

592
00:42:13,041 --> 00:42:15,666
One, two, three. Here, Dad.

593
00:42:16,791 --> 00:42:18,250
Yes, okay.

594
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:19,833
Okay.

595
00:42:32,833 --> 00:42:36,458
REAL ESTATE AGENT

596
00:42:50,208 --> 00:42:51,041
Here.

597
00:43:47,291 --> 00:43:48,708
What are you looking at?

598
00:43:51,625 --> 00:43:53,541
Stop checking. You look handsome.

599
00:44:17,250 --> 00:44:18,458
Dad, do you remember?

600
00:44:18,541 --> 00:44:21,500
You used to host
those watermelon seed spitting contests.

601
00:44:21,583 --> 00:44:22,708
Remember?

602
00:44:23,333 --> 00:44:25,250
Here, look. Like this.

603
00:44:25,333 --> 00:44:26,333
Let me show you.

604
00:44:27,583 --> 00:44:28,583
Watch me spit it.

605
00:44:32,583 --> 00:44:33,708
Remember?

606
00:44:34,541 --> 00:44:36,083
You always won.

607
00:44:36,625 --> 00:44:37,916
Okay, I did win once.

608
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:39,833
But I knew you lost on purpose.

609
00:44:40,541 --> 00:44:42,708
I'll give you a piece, okay?

610
00:44:44,166 --> 00:44:45,000
Here.

611
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:46,333
Take a bite.

612
00:44:47,916 --> 00:44:48,833
Come on.

613
00:44:49,375 --> 00:44:50,541
You always won.

614
00:44:52,625 --> 00:44:54,541
And when you won, you did this dance.

615
00:44:55,333 --> 00:44:56,166
Remember?

616
00:44:59,791 --> 00:45:01,375
We always danced when it rained.

617
00:45:01,458 --> 00:45:04,375
Do you remember dancing in the rain?

618
00:45:05,208 --> 00:45:06,291
Remember?

619
00:45:07,416 --> 00:45:08,541
Come on. Hurry up.

620
00:45:08,625 --> 00:45:09,541
Give it a go.

621
00:45:10,791 --> 00:45:12,791
I know you can win this. Here.

622
00:45:18,708 --> 00:45:20,416
Okay, that's fine.

623
00:45:23,166 --> 00:45:24,666
It's okay if you can't remember.

624
00:45:29,541 --> 00:45:30,458
It's okay.

625
00:45:52,875 --> 00:45:56,000
I ASKED YANI TO ADD YOU
YOU CAN MAKE AN APPOINTMENT WITH HER

626
00:45:56,083 --> 00:45:58,291
Hey, what are you doing?

627
00:46:03,375 --> 00:46:05,958
What's up? I don't know…

628
00:46:51,083 --> 00:46:52,583
You look dashing.

629
00:46:54,333 --> 00:46:56,083
Why are you so handsome?

630
00:47:06,666 --> 00:47:07,583
Cheng Kuang-chi.

631
00:47:08,708 --> 00:47:09,541
So dashing.

632
00:47:10,791 --> 00:47:11,875
<i>I'll take a photo.</i>

633
00:47:14,208 --> 00:47:15,750
From the reflection.

634
00:47:28,500 --> 00:47:30,250
You're feeling great today?

635
00:47:47,583 --> 00:47:50,125
Hello, sir. I am Yani.

636
00:47:50,208 --> 00:47:53,166
Dad, this is Chia-yun's friend, Yani.

637
00:47:53,250 --> 00:47:57,333
She'll look after you for two days.
She's very experienced and really nice.

638
00:47:57,416 --> 00:47:59,375
So don't worry, okay?

639
00:48:00,541 --> 00:48:03,625
He's a bit shy, but when he knows you,
he cracks lots of jokes.

640
00:48:03,708 --> 00:48:05,916
No problem, madam.
I'll take good care of him.

641
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:08,125
I'll be home around 8:00 p.m.

642
00:48:08,208 --> 00:48:10,166
- It's a bit late. Sorry about that.
- Okay.

643
00:48:10,250 --> 00:48:12,416
No worries, madam. I'll take care of him.

644
00:48:12,500 --> 00:48:14,333
- Don't worry. Bye.
- Thank you. Okay.

645
00:48:14,416 --> 00:48:15,833
- Bye, madam. Bye.
- Thank you.

646
00:48:18,083 --> 00:48:20,083
Sir, I am Yani.

647
00:48:20,166 --> 00:48:21,458
I'm here to look after you.

648
00:48:21,541 --> 00:48:22,708
Don't be afraid.

649
00:48:23,208 --> 00:48:25,000
Sir, what food would you like?

650
00:48:26,208 --> 00:48:29,166
I was a tour guide,

651
00:48:29,250 --> 00:48:33,875
so I think I'm good
at handling unexpected incidents.

652
00:48:33,958 --> 00:48:36,208
- So you are experienced.
- Yes.

653
00:48:36,291 --> 00:48:39,166
- And also good at handling crises.
- That's right.

654
00:48:39,250 --> 00:48:41,333
Great. You're exactly what we need.

655
00:48:41,416 --> 00:48:42,416
Yes.

656
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:44,458
So why at this age…

657
00:48:44,541 --> 00:48:45,583
Sorry, I mean…

658
00:48:54,375 --> 00:48:57,583
Sir, I've looked after many people,

659
00:48:57,666 --> 00:49:00,375
so I understand how you feel.

660
00:49:01,916 --> 00:49:04,041
I'll take good care of you.

661
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:09,125
I haven't seen my own dad for a long time.

662
00:49:10,208 --> 00:49:11,583
Isn't that funny?

663
00:49:11,666 --> 00:49:13,375
I don't take care of my dad,

664
00:49:13,458 --> 00:49:15,833
but I keep
taking care of other people's dads.

665
00:49:20,375 --> 00:49:22,541
How about I play some music for you?

666
00:49:24,958 --> 00:49:26,541
Sir, do you want some water?

667
00:49:26,625 --> 00:49:28,250
I'll get you some, okay?

668
00:49:55,750 --> 00:49:59,708
Hello, Yani? I'm sorry, I was sleeping
and missed my stop. What's wrong?

669
00:49:59,791 --> 00:50:02,916
Madam, your dad
locked me out when I took the trash out.

670
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:04,541
<i>- I can't get in now.</i>
- What?

671
00:50:05,291 --> 00:50:06,125
It's okay.

672
00:50:06,208 --> 00:50:07,375
Is he okay?

673
00:50:07,458 --> 00:50:09,125
<i>I don't know.</i>

674
00:50:09,208 --> 00:50:11,041
Okay, listen. I'll be home soon.

675
00:50:11,125 --> 00:50:13,375
Stay by the door and don't go anywhere.

676
00:50:13,458 --> 00:50:14,791
I'll be right back.

677
00:50:14,875 --> 00:50:15,750
<i>Okay, bye.</i>

678
00:50:28,041 --> 00:50:29,583
- Madam, you're home.
- Sorry.

679
00:50:30,083 --> 00:50:31,458
- Hurry.
- Okay.

680
00:50:35,625 --> 00:50:36,916
Cheng Kuang-chi!

681
00:50:39,250 --> 00:50:40,166
She hit me!

682
00:50:40,250 --> 00:50:41,166
I didn't.

683
00:50:41,250 --> 00:50:43,750
- I didn't hit him.
- She really did.

684
00:50:43,833 --> 00:50:45,625
- I know.
- I've been looking after him.

685
00:50:45,708 --> 00:50:47,083
- I didn't hit him.
- I know.

686
00:50:47,166 --> 00:50:48,708
I'm so sorry.

687
00:50:48,791 --> 00:50:51,125
I think your dad
doesn't like having me here.

688
00:50:51,208 --> 00:50:53,166
No, he's just not used to it.

689
00:50:53,250 --> 00:50:55,583
You know, he has good and bad days.

690
00:50:55,666 --> 00:50:58,208
- I really didn't hit him.
- Sorry. I know you didn't.

691
00:50:58,291 --> 00:50:59,791
Why don't you go home and rest?

692
00:50:59,875 --> 00:51:01,041
Sorry I kept you waiting.

693
00:51:01,125 --> 00:51:02,375
It's way over time now.

694
00:51:02,458 --> 00:51:03,833
- Okay, I'll go now.
- Sorry.

695
00:51:03,916 --> 00:51:05,041
- Thank you.
- I'm off.

696
00:51:05,125 --> 00:51:06,166
Yani, I'm sorry.

697
00:51:06,250 --> 00:51:08,250
Can you give my dad another chance?

698
00:51:08,333 --> 00:51:09,708
I'll think about it, okay?

699
00:51:09,791 --> 00:51:11,375
- Yani, I'm so sorry.
- Sorry, madam.

700
00:51:11,458 --> 00:51:12,416
I'll go now.

701
00:51:12,500 --> 00:51:14,583
Okay, please do think about it. Please.

702
00:51:18,791 --> 00:51:19,708
She hit me.

703
00:51:27,583 --> 00:51:29,208
Okay, let's get you to sit up.

704
00:51:29,291 --> 00:51:31,000
One, two, three.

705
00:51:36,708 --> 00:51:37,916
Are you hurt?

706
00:51:45,333 --> 00:51:46,166
Slippers.

707
00:52:22,166 --> 00:52:24,333
I'm Cheng Kuang-chi.

708
00:52:25,875 --> 00:52:29,333
My daughter is Cheng Le-le.

709
00:52:44,250 --> 00:52:45,166
Do you remember

710
00:52:46,083 --> 00:52:47,875
your daughter loves you?

711
00:52:57,500 --> 00:53:00,000
Do you know your daughter loves you a lot?

712
00:53:05,791 --> 00:53:07,041
Yes.

713
00:53:09,625 --> 00:53:10,500
I do.

714
00:53:17,208 --> 00:53:20,083
It's okay if you don't remember anything.

715
00:53:22,166 --> 00:53:24,750
Just remember
your daughter loves you very much.

716
00:53:25,791 --> 00:53:26,875
I…

717
00:53:27,375 --> 00:53:28,625
I know that.

718
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:30,916
I know.

719
00:53:33,791 --> 00:53:35,375
But you're such a bad boy.

720
00:53:39,375 --> 00:53:40,541
I'm mad at you.

721
00:53:47,041 --> 00:53:48,291
<i>Mr. Cheng Kuang-chi.</i>

722
00:53:48,375 --> 00:53:50,666
You look handsome today. Good boy.

723
00:53:50,750 --> 00:53:51,833
Ten out of ten.

724
00:53:51,916 --> 00:53:55,333
Look, you have a great daughter.
She's always by your side.

725
00:53:55,875 --> 00:53:57,875
I'll prescribe
a month's repeat prescription.

726
00:53:57,958 --> 00:54:00,583
We'll check again when he's more stable.

727
00:54:00,666 --> 00:54:02,208
Okay. Thank you.

728
00:54:09,208 --> 00:54:10,041
Thank you.

729
00:54:27,625 --> 00:54:28,833
Whoa…

730
00:54:29,375 --> 00:54:31,500
Dad, it's raining. Give me a minute.

731
00:54:32,208 --> 00:54:33,875
I remember I brought an umbrella.

732
00:54:36,541 --> 00:54:37,916
It's hard to grasp.

733
00:54:48,625 --> 00:54:50,250
Dad!

734
00:54:50,333 --> 00:54:51,750
Dad, what are you doing?

735
00:54:55,416 --> 00:54:56,625
It's raining! You…

736
00:56:33,458 --> 00:56:36,291
<i>Since the rain won't stop anytime soon,</i>

737
00:56:38,333 --> 00:56:39,875
<i>I'll stay by your side,</i>

738
00:56:41,333 --> 00:56:43,333
<i>just like you did for me.</i>

739
01:00:30,833 --> 01:00:35,833
